  "text": "Anemia was induced in adult (2-5 months old) female animals as described before [CITATION_1] . Briefly, we injected animals with 1ml of 5% phenylhydrazine (Sigma Aldrich, P26252) solution daily for 4 days. At day 5 after beginning of injections, blood was collected from phenylhydrazine-treated and control animals. According to Brilliant Cresyl Blue staining, proportion of immature erythrocytes at this point was ∼ 95% (189 out of 200 counted cells) in treated animals and 3.5% (9 out of 256 counted cells) in control animals.",
